encyclopedia.content: non 副词 ad. 1. 【拉】非；不 名词 n. 1. 【法】反对票；投反对票的人 non- 前缀 pref. 1. 表示"非","不","无"(non可以和许多字组成复合字，可连写或加连字符；但若第二字字首为大写时，则必须加连字符，如：non-Opec) non 1. 非，无，不 2. 不，非 3. 你：侬

entry.tran: (置于形容词和名词前构成形容词，指不具有某一特质或特定方面)表示“非”，“无”
entry.def: Non- is used in front of adjectives and nouns to form adjectives that describe something as not having a particular quality or feature.

entry.tran: (置于名词前构成名词，指某一特定行动尚未或不会发生)表示“不”，“未”
entry.def: Non- is used in front of nouns to form nouns which refer to situations where a particular action has not or will not take place.

example.ex: He was disqualified from the council for non-attendance...
example.tran: 他因缺席而被该委员会免除了资格。

example.ex: Both countries agreed that normal relations would be based on non-interference in each other's internal affairs.
example.tran: 两国一致同意正常邦交关系应建立在互不干涉内政的基础之上。

entry.tran: (置于名词前构成名词，指不属于某一特定群体或类别的人)表示“非”，“不”
entry.def: Non- is used in front of nouns to form nouns which refer to people who do not belong to a particular group or category.

example.ex: Children of smokers are more likely to start smoking than are children of non-smokers.
example.tran: 吸烟者的子女比不吸烟者的子女更有可能会抽烟。
